{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> περί-στᾰσις</b>, εως, ἡ, <br /> <b>standing round</b>, τίς ἥδε κραυγὴ καὶ δόμων π.; <b>crowds standing round</b> the house, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Teleclides Comicus 35 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; π. ποιεῖσθαι, of crowds, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Characteres” 8.12 (_plural_); ὄχλοιο π. Timo 34.1 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: hence, in concretesense, <b>crowd standing round</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 1.32.3, 18.53.11. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>surrounding</b>, ἡ τοῦ ψυχροῦ π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Problemata” 869a21 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: in concrete sense, <b>environment</b>, π. ἀέρος ψυχροῦ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Epistulae” 2p.50U., compare p.48 U.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>surrounding space</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 6.31.1, 6.41.2 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; especially <b>free space round</b> a building, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “OGI” 483.123, +others (Pergam., 2nd c.AD), “IG” 14.352i8, 70 (from Halaesa). \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__2.b</b></Level4> <b>portico surrounding</b> a hall or temple, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work]42(1).102.6 (Epid., 4th c.BC), 3rd c.BC(?): Callixinus Historicus 1; ἡ ἔξω π. τοῦ σηκοῦ “IG” 7.3073.90 (Lebad.). \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__2.c</b></Level4> <b>district surrounding</b> a village, <b>neighbourhood,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PTeb. 14.19 (2nd c.BC), +others \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>circumstances, situation, state of affairs</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 1.35.10, 4.67.4, etc.; αἱ π. [τῶν πόλεων] [prev. author] 10.21.3 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+